Liverpool moved up to second in the Premier League as they overcame a stubborn Brentford side to take all three points at Anfield. Fabinho’s far-post header eased some of the tension that had built up at Anfield over 43 goalless minutes, but the home fans were relieved when Bryan Mbeumo sliced wide from a fine position after the break.   Leeds beat West Ham 3-2 at London Stadium     UPDATED: Everton sack Benitez as coach     Football enthusiasts laud Sanwo-Olu’s viewing centre…   Shortly afterwards, Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain connected with an Andy Robertson cross to double the lead and Takumi Minamino came off the bench to side-foot home a third. Leaders Manchester City are 11 points above Liverpool, having played a game more.   - Advertisement - BBC Sport